Prepare the data
As you may recall in your training, making a chart usually takes two steps: Preparing the data, then plotting the data.
To prepare this data for your plot, you need to:

Group_by species and summarize the number of rows. Name the new variable count_species.
Arrange the result so the highest count is at the top.
Drop any NA values.
We are saving the result into a new dataframe called species_data. We print that out at the end.
















Solution







species_data &lt;- starwars |&gt;
  group_by(species) |&gt;
  summarize(count_species = n()) |&gt;
  arrange(desc(count_species)) |&gt;
  drop_na()

